Preheat your oven to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Put a large #saucepan{} of water with @salt{1/2%tsp} on to boil for the potatoes.

Chop the @potatoes{450%g} into 2cm chunks (no need to peel). Pick the @tarragon{1/2%bunch} leaves from their stalks and roughly chop (discard the stalks). Grate the @mature Cheddar cheese{30%g}. Halve any thick @Tenderstem® broccoli{150%g} stems.

Wrap a rasher of @British streaky bacon{4%rashers} around each @British Cumberland sausages{4} - starting at the top, spiral the rasher down the sausage so it covers the whole thing.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw meat.

Pop the sausages on a #baking tray{} and roast on the middle shelf of your oven until golden brown and cooked through, ~{20-25%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: The sausages are cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Meanwhile, once your pan of water is boiling, add the potatoes. Cook until you can easily slip a knife through, ~{15-20%minutes}.

After ~{10-12%minutes}, add the @chopped kale{100%g} to the same pan. Cook for the remaining time until both are tender, ~{5-8%minutes}.

Halfway through cooking, drizzle the @honey{15%g} over the sausages, mix well to coat and move to one side of the baking tray.

> TIP: If your honey has hardened, pop in a bowl of hot water for 1 min.

At the same time, add the broccoli to the other side of the baking tray.

> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

Drizzle with @oil{for roasting}, season with @salt{} and @black pepper{}, then toss to coat. Roast for the remaining time until tender and crispy, ~{10-12%minutes}.

Meanwhile, heat a small #frying pan{} on medium heat (no oil).

Pour in the @water{75%ml}(for the sauce), @chicken stock paste{10%g}, @wholegrain mustard{17%g}, tarragon and half the @creme fraiche{150%g}. Stir together, then bring to the boil.

Reduce the heat to medium-low and simmer until slightly thickened, ~{2-3%minutes}. Season to taste with salt and pepper if needed, then remove from the heat and set aside until ready to serve.

Once the potatoes and kale cooked, drain them both in a #colander{} and return to the pan, off the heat.

Add the remaining creme fraiche and roughly mash together with a #potato masher{}.

Stir through the cheese, then season to taste with salt and pepper. Cover with a #lid{} to keep warm.

When everything's ready, reheat the mustard sauce if necessary. Add a splash of water if it's a little too thick.

Serve your sticky pigs in blankets with the colcannon and Tenderstem® alongside.

Spoon over the mustard sauce to finish.

Enjoy!